<cadsofttools version="2">
<!-- Description: buttonmenu command enables you to add/remove/activate user buttons in the ribbon. -->
<!-- Attribute description -->
<!-- Mode is a mandatory attribute. The possible values are "ADD/DEL/EN/DIS". ADD –adds a button. DEL – Removes a button. EN – enables a button. DIS – disables a button -->
<!-- Caption is a mandatory attribute. This is a displayed button name as well as a unique id of the user button -->
<!-- Page is a mandatory attribute if Mode="ADD". This is the name of the tab in the ribbon where you wish to add the button -->
<!-- ToolBar is a mandatory attribute if Mode="ADD". The is the name of the toolbar in the ribbon where you wish to add the button -->
<!-- Type is a mandatory attribute if Mode="ADD". It can take the following values: "1/2/3", where "1" – stands for a big button, the icon size is 32*32, "2" – stands for a small button without caption, "3" – stands for a small button with a caption. For "2" and "3" the icon size is 16*16 -->
<!-- To add a button with an icon, use the subcommand icon -->
<!-- The subcommand icon uses base64 to transmit the data. It can have the following attributes -->
<!-- img – contains an icon in base64 format -->
<!-- Mode determines for which button mode the icon is used. The value "0" means that the image is used for the activated button. The value "1" means that the icon is used for the inactive button -->

<!-- You will find examples below -->

